https://www.baeldung.com/spring-cloud-configuration

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Setup JCE
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
JCE: Java Cryptography Extension

- put the jars extracted from jce_policy-8.zip to
/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/**< jdk_v>**/Contents/Home/jre/lib/security

- download JCS for Java 8
https://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/jce8-download-2133166.html

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
generate keystore
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-> simple alternative: set the encrypt.key for symmetric encryption

- keytool -genkeypair -alias config-server-key \
         -keyalg RSA -keysize 4096 -sigalg SHA512withRSA \
         -dname 'CN=Config Server,OU=Spring Cloud,O=Baeldung' \
         -keypass my-k34-s3cr3t -keystore config-server.jks \
         -storepass my-s70r3-s3cr3t

- put generated config-server.jks file to /resources

- add encrypt.keystore.* properties to bootstrap.properties
 (https://github.com/spring-cloud/spring-cloud-config/issues/1111)

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
encrypt/decrypt values with endpoints
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
https://cloud.spring.io/spring-cloud-config/reference/html/#_encryption_and_decryption

(doesn't work)

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
encrypt/decrypt values spring boot cli
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# symmetric
    $ spring encrypt mysecret --key foo

# asymmetric, with keystore
    $ spring encrypt mysecret --key @${HOME}/.ssh/id_rsa.pub
